 "description": "Hexes per day by mount and vessel (Man 3, Draft Horse 5, Light Horse 10, Galley 20…, flyers 15-48 per the tables); parties over 100 lose a hex, over 1,000 two. Terrain per OUTDOOR SURVIVAL: mountains/swamps 3 per hex, non-ford river crossings 3, woods/deserts 2; mountain tracks 2, wood/swamp tracks none. Rest one full day in six (Dragons: a week per three walking weeks, three weeks after flying ones). A hex spans about 5 miles; each move is a day, each day a turn.",
